    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-27T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="940"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d940">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/423: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-28T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 28, 1937—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1238. Reference Department’s 697, December 27, 11 a.m.<note n="58"
                        xml:id="d940fn58">Not printed.</note> Allison and staff have sailed on the
                        <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi>. In paragraph 2 of my 1231, December 26, 6 p.m.,
                    I said that our officers were asked to postpone departure for Nanking until
                    after 1st of January. Japanese Consul General estimated it would require 3 or 4
                    days to proceed from Shanghai to Nanking and expected situation at Nanking to be
                    sufficiently cleared after about the 4th of January. Allison understands
                    this.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi> may visit Wuhu before proceeding to
                        Nanking. If so Allison will investigate the flag incident mentioned in my
                        No, 1219.<note n="59" xml:id="d940fn59">December 23, 9 p.m., <ref
                                target="frus1937v04#pg_409">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iv</hi>, p.
                                409</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Allison has been supplied two gray codes and special gray cipher.
                            Espy<note n="60" xml:id="d940fn60">James Espy, Vice Consul at Shanghai
                            on special detail to Nanking.</note> has the post’s consular rubber
                        stamp seal.</item>
                </list>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
